<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paris Opens Children's Village for New Year's Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The French capital Paris opened
on Friday a Swiss-style children's winter village in the garden of
Trocadero opposite the Tower Eiffel across the Seine River.
</P>
<P>
The village consists of wooden chalets, snow, fir trees from
the eastern region of Savoie bordering Switzerland, a skating
ground, a snowboard track and a Christmas market.
</P>
<P>
All the children can have a free entry into the village until
January 10, said the Paris city hall, which built the village with
both private and public funds.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises joining the project will also invite children to
chalets of activities to play multimedia machines, join making-up
parties, and draw pictures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
