<HEADLINE> FIFA Irrigated with Brazilian Federation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- World football
governing body FIFA on Friday was irrigated with a legal case
being made against the Brazilian Football Confederation (CBF) by
two football clubs in the civil courts and threatened to suspend
CBF.
</P>
<P>
FIFA said in a statement that the CBF must solve the issue
before it imposed a suspension on the federation.
</P>
<P>
Sao Paulo's player Sandro Hiroshi falsified his date of birth
on all documents and Sao Paulo was deducted points for fielding
the player in a win over Botafogo, which was relegated to the
second division because of the loss.
</P>
<P>
But Gama considered that Botofago had unfairly been awarded the
points and wants them return to Sao Paulo. That would mean that
Gama would return to the top flight.
</P>
<P>
Sao Paulo and Gama took legal action against the CBF after
their complaints were refused by CBF president Ricardo Texeira.
</P>
