<HEADLINE> Britain Expects Iraq Agreement at UN on Friday: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Britain said on Friday that it
expected the United Nations Security Council to agree a new
resolution on Iraqi sanctions at a vote on Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"The new resolution on Iraq is likely to be agreed at the
United Nations at 1045 New York time," a spokesman for Prime
Minister Tony Blair said.
</P>
<P>
"It is a tough but fair resolution," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said the new resolution would include an improved oil-for-
food program to assist Iraqi civilians.
</P>
<P>
The resolution, if reached, will make an end of sanctions
conditional on Iraq's full compliance with 120 days of weapons
inspections.
</P>
<P>
It will automatically lift the revenue cap on Iraqi oil sales
under the oil-for-food program, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
But he made no comment on how the other members of the 15-
strong Security Council were expected to vote.  
</P>
