<HEADLINE> Thailand's CP Companies to Form "Kitchen of World" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's agro-industrial
giant,Charoen Pokphand Group (CP), revealed its ambition to be "
kitchen of the world" by merging all of its livestock and
agricultural businesses in Thailand into one, the group announced
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Charoen Pokphand Feedmill Public Company Ltd. changed its name
to Charoen Pokphand Foods Public Company Ltd. (CPF), acquiring
three of the group's listed companies on the Stock Exchange of
Thailand (SET)by share swapping in November 1998.
</P>
<P>
The delisting date of the three companies will be on December
20,1999, the group said in a press release Friday.
</P>
<P>
Six other non-listed agribusiness companies of the group were
also acquired by the new CPF in early January 1999.
</P>
<P>
CP said in the press release that CPF is "dedicated to
producing high quality food products to satisfy consumer needs the
world over."
</P>
<P>
CP executives said that a "Under CPF" sign will be labeled on
all the foodstuff produced in Thailand, from eggs, chickens, milk
to sausages and hamburgers, which will still keep their original
brand names.
</P>
<P>
The hallmark will help the consumers to recognize the company
as a whole, they said.
</P>
<P>
CPF reported sales of 39.5 billion baht (1.02 billion U.S.
dollars)and net profit of 3.3 billion baht (85.7 million dollars)
in the first nine months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
