<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Grant Women One Third key Positions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The supreme organ of the ruling
Zimbabwe African National Union (Patriotic Front), the Political
Bureau Friday agreed to give women one third of the key positions
both in the party and government.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after the second day deliberations of the Third
National Congress, Secretary for Information and Publicity Nathan
Shamuyarira told reporters that this had to be ratified by the
congress.
</P>
<P>
Presenting a summary of the Central Committee report at the
start of the congress, President and First Secretary of the Zanu
(PF) Robert Magabe said women had indicated to the party that they
wanted a quota system in which they should be given a third of the
party's and government's key positions.
</P>
<P>
Women who the backbone of Zanu (PF) but are marginalized in the
higher positions within the party and government. 
</P>
