<HEADLINE> London Stock Market Closes Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 17 (Xinhua) - European stock markets ended
mostly higher Friday on a wave of fresh enthusiasm for technology
and telecom stocks.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 climbed 52.6 points, or 0.8 percent, to close
at 6724.6, just 18 points away of a record set on December 3rd.
</P>
<P>
The index got a hefty boost from BT, which jumped 5.1 percent
as investors continued to snap up phone stocks. Sector rival Colt
Telecom steamed up 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Software developer Sage (SGE) advanced 2.4 percent, while tech
firm Sema (SEM) leapt 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The electronically traded Xetra Dax in Frankfurt added 12.61
points to close at 6353.90. A rise of 256 points on the week.
</P>
<P>
Paris' CAC 40 ended down 0.7 percent at 5502.40 points, up 21.3
since last Friday after giving up an early technical boost
provided by the expiration of Dow Jones Stock index futures.
</P>
</TEXT>
