<HEADLINE> Canada Unveils Multimillion-Dollar Support for Homeless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Labor Minister
Claudette Bradshaw has promised 753 million Canadian dollars (
about 508 million U.S. dollars) for the country's homeless over
three years.
</P>
<P>
"Today's announcement is an important step towards eliminating
homelessness in this country," the minister told a news conference
Friday in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Under a Supporting Communities Partnership Initiative, the
federal government plans to allocate part of its huge budget
surplus to a housing project joined by provinces, municipalities,
as well as private and voluntary sectors.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed at building more affordable housing,
upgrading low-income buildings and finding more shelter for the
homeless. 
</P>
