<HEADLINE> DRC Rebels Seek A United Front in Uganda Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wamba dia Wamba, political leader of the Congolese Rally for
Democracy (RCD) based in Kisangani, said on Friday, "we are
trying to form a common front in order to implement the Lusaka
agreement better."
</P>
<P>
The leaders of both RCD factions and the leader of Congolese
Liberation Movement Pierre Bemba held informal talks Friday in
Kabale to make preparations for the two-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting came after both the rebel groups and the DRC
government agreed Tuesday to choose former Botswanan President
Ketumile Masire as the facilitator in the political dialogue under
the Lusaka peace accord.
</P>
<P>
RCD, which took up arms in August 1998 to topple DRC President
Laurent Kabila, split into rival factions led by Emile Illunga and
Wamba dia Wamba respectively in May this year due to
irreconcilable differences over strategies, with Uganda and Rwanda
behind each of them.  
</P>
