<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Ruling Party's Membership Tops Two </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Membership of the ruling
Zimbabwe African National Union (Patriotic Front) (Zanu-PF) has
topped over two million, Information and Publicity Secretary of
the party Nathan Shamuyarira said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Briefing reporters on the second day of the third Zanu (PF)
National Congress in Harare, Shamuyarira added that the party's
membership continued to grow.
</P>
<P>
"You go into any village or community you will find a Zanu (PF)
branch. The party has a strong grass-roots support," he said.
</P>
<P>
The party's Political Commissar Moven Mahachi, however, said
earlier that factionalism was threatening the growth of the party
and that it had to be ended.
</P>
<P>
The Zanu (PF) was formed in 1963 and in 1987 it merged with the
rival Zimbabwe African People's Union led by the late
Vice-President Joshua Nkomo.
</P>
<P>
The party has been in power since independence in 1980 under
the leadership of President Robert Mugabe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
