<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Completes First Off-Market Gold Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) announced Friday that it had completed the first off-
market gold sale last Tuesday under the previously announced
financing plan for debt relief and financial support for the world
's poorest countries.
</P>
<P>
"We sold slightly more than 7 million ounces of gold to Brazil,
" said IMF Treasurer Eduard Brau, "and accepted it back
immediately from Brazil for payment of an obligation due the same
day. Thus, the gold did not enter the market."
</P>
<P>
The IMF retained about 342.5 million U.S. dollars on its own
account as required by the Articles of Agreement. The remainder of
the proceeds totaling 1.6 billion dollars was invested with the
Bank for International Settlements to generate income for the
Heavily Indebted Poor Countries Initiative.
</P>
<P>
The next sale, which will amount to about 655,000 ounces, will
be completed Friday, the IMF said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
