<HEADLINE> Legislation For Protecting Wild Animal and Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Ma Fu, deputy-director of the
State Forestry Administration (SFA) of China, said today that
China will improve laws and regulations on protecting wild animals
and plants.
</P>
<P>
The administration is expected to finish drafting regulations
on wild fauna and the import-export of plants soon. It is also
working hard to complete the drafting of regulations on wetland
protection by next year.
</P>
<P>
The SFA will make a complete list of wild animals and plants to
formulate protective and priority measures, said Ma on the last
day of a National Conference on Wild Animal and Plants Protection.
</P>
<P>
Ma advised forest departments across the country to accelerate
drafting and implementing local regulations and make a list of the
wild plants that will be designated for protection in 2000.
</P>
<P>
Provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities which have yet
to issue local regulations for the protection of wild animals have
until 2001 do to so.
</P>
<P>
China has issued a series of laws and regulations, including
the Forest Law and Regulations on Natural Reserve Protection to
further strengthen the protection of wild animals and plants.
Local governments have also promulgated more than 40 regulations.
</P>
</TEXT>
