</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that sports would be an active role in
the drive to build Singapore a more important world-class city.
</P>
<P>
He said "We have only survived but also prospered because we
dared to achieve - and to excel in whatever we do."
</P>
<P>
With this can-do spirit, Goh said he had earlier set three
challenges for all Singapore's athletes.
</P>
<P>
"These challenges are: an Olympic gold in sailing, a place in
the Thomas Cup finals and qualification in the Asian Group for the
World Cup soccer finals," he said.
</P>
<P>
Goh urged Singaporeans to learn from New Zealand which has
produce world beaters in middle-distance running, rugby, yacht
racing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
