<HEADLINE> France's Brittany Region Chooses Hero of Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 18 (Xinhua) -- France's western region of
Brittany has chosen the lone high seas salesman Eric Tabarly as
the "Briton of the century."
</P>
<P>
Tabarly disappeared from his boat on July 13 off the coast of
Wales, Britain, during a tempest.
</P>
<P>
He was said to have been struck and knocked over board while on
the deck of his boat and his body was never recovered.
</P>
<P>
Some suspect the 66-year-old salesman had chosen his own way of
death because he had often told his friends of his intention to "
marry" the sea.
</P>
<P>
In a poll published on Saturday among 601 Britons, 80 percent
chose Tabarly as the hero of the century.
</P>
<P>
A historically Celtic region with a strong nationalist
sentiment, Brittany is known for producing good sportsmen and
singers.
</P>
<P>
The poll also showed that most of the Britons regard the on-
going pollution crisis off its coast, which was caused by the
incident of the oil tanker "Erika" last week, as the most
important event of the century in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
