<HEADLINE> France to Increase Investment in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Consul General of France in
Hong Kong and Macao Jerome Pasquier said in a recent interview
that France firmly supports China's resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Macao and will continue to increase French
investment in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Pasquier said that he is confident about the future of Macao
and its return to the motherland will bring new opportunities for
French businesses there.
</P>
<P>
Pasquier believes that the "one country, two systems" concept
will work well in Macao as it did in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a historic date. I totally share the great joy and
pleasure with the Chinese people," he said.
</P>
<P>
As an envoy, Pasquier has traveled frequently between Hong Kong
and Macao since he took office in Hong Kong last year. He has also
met with Edmund Ho Hau Wah, chief executive-designate of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (MSAR) several times.
</P>
<P>
"The people in Macao are very optimistic of Macao's future, and
the capable MSAR leaders have lots of new ideas to run things well,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
Macao's return will benefit not only its own economic
development and social stability, but also the foreign trade and
investment there, he said.
</P>
<P>
The French government attaches great importance to China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Macao and will send
a high-profile delegation to attend the handover ceremony since
France is one of the biggest European investors in Macao, Pasquier
said.
</P>
<P>
"We have had a good economic presence in Macao and we have many
French companies there dealing with water supply, electricity,
waste treatment, air transport, hotel and entertainment," Pasquier
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
