<HEADLINE> Scientists Remember Marshal Nie Rongzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The centennial of the late
Marshal Nie Rongzhen (1899-1992) was marked today at the Chinese
Academy of Sciences. Nie was a founder of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army and New China.
</P>
<P>
At a forum attended by scientists, Zhu Lilan, the minister of
Science and Technology spoke highly of Nie's great contributions
to science and technology, saying that Nie helped implement major
policy decisions in developing science and technology in the
country.
</P>
<P>
As a prominent leader of the sector of science and technology
for national defense, Nie is also remembered for his contributions
to the development of missiles, satellites and the atom and
hydrogen bombs in China, which substantially improved the strength
of China's national defense. 
</P>
