<HEADLINE> Gold, Silver Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Prices of gold and silver
shot up further on the bullion market Saturday in Mumbai (Bombay)
on persistent industrial and local demand.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold rose by 20 rupees (0.46 U.S. dollar) to end at 4,
460 rupees (103.71 dollars) per 10 grams from the previous close
of 4,440 rupees (103.25 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two-carat gold was nominally quoted better at 4,125
rupees(95.93 dollars) per 10 grams from Friday's level of 4,110
rupees(95.58 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) moved up by 15 rupees (
0.35 dollar) to 8,140 rupees (189.31 dollars) per kilogram, from
the last close of 8,125 rupees (188.96 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) also shot up moderately to 8,010
rupees(186.28 dollars) as compared to 8,000 rupees (186.05 dollars)
per kg.
</P>
</TEXT>
