<HEADLINE> Chinese College Students Look Forward to Macao's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- All books on Macao at Nankai
University in north China's Tianjin Municipality have been lent
out as students learn more about the future special administrative
region.
</P>
<P>
College students decorated the campus with blossoms and banners
and held various activities such as parties, concerts, seminars
and general knowledge contests to welcome the return of Macao on
December 20.
</P>
<P>
Students in the Chemistry Department folded 100,000 paper
cranes which will be released in the air with 1,999 hydrogen
balloons to celebrate Macao's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Macao university students receive invitation letters almost
every day. Yao Zaixing, a student at the Finance Department of
Nankai University said that Macao's pending return to the
motherland fills him with an incredible sense of warmth.
</P>
<P>
Beijing opened a website relating to Macao early this month so
that tertiary students could communicate and express their
feelings towards the pending Macao handover.
</P>
<P>
Over 10,000 students from universities in east China's Jiangsu
Province will sign their names and write down their wishes for
Macao on a 1,000-meter-long scroll.
</P>
<P>
Several thousand college students from Beijing will attend a
gala party tomorrow night at Tian'anmen Square. 
</P>
</TEXT>
