<HEADLINE> Schifferer Claims First Win in Val Gardena Downhill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Andreas Schifferer won
his first World Cup downhill this season in Val Gardena, Italy, on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Schifferer, the 1998 World Cup downhill champion, took the win
with a time of two minutes 04.78 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italian Kristian Ghedina, who won a downhill in Val Gardena on
Friday, hoped to be the first man since Franz Klammer 23 years ago
to win back-to-back races here, but failed and took the second
place in 2:04.89.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Hermann Maier, the reigning world champion, finished
third in 2:05.00. 
</P>
</TEXT>
