<HEADLINE> Premature Baby Survives in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 18 (Xinhua) -- A premature baby, weighing only
615 grams, has survived 103 days of medical treatment and was
discharged from hospital here today.
</P>
<P>
According to doctors of a government hospital, the baby infant
is the lightest and smallest baby ever born to Macao.
</P>
<P>
The baby's mother gave birth in early September when she had
only about 25 weeks of pregnancy. The baby boy had been under
intensive care in the hospital, including 31 days depending on
respiration machines.
</P>
<P>
According to physicians Wong Fong Ian and Lui Kin Man, the
baby, with the given name Zhijian (meaning bright and healthy in
Chinese) now weighs 2,300 grams and is as healthy as babies at his
age.
</P>
</TEXT>
