<HEADLINE> Air Pollution in Tehran Hits Danger Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Air pollution in the Iranian
capital city of Tehran has reached the "danger" level on Saturday
and the situation will continue in the coming days, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The intensity of the two pollutants, carbon monoxide and
suspended particles, has hit the "danger" level while other
pollutants increased considerably, said the Iranian Weather Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The Bureau predicted that the polluted stagnant air would remain
unchanged at least by Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
Residents in Tehran are advised not to travel in the city in
their personal cars but to take public transportation instead.
</P>
<P>
Elementary and primary schools were recently closed due to the
air pollution, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Over two million old vehicles which consume fuel more than the
standard are the main cause of about 80 percent of air pollution in
Tehran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
