<HEADLINE> South Korea to Open New Sea Routes to China, Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 18 (Xinhua) -- South Korea will open four new
commercial sea routes linking with China and Russia next year, the
Maritime and Fisheries Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The new sea lanes will include those for ferries and container
ships.
</P>
<P>
The first ferry route from Mokpo city of South Korea to
Lianyungang city of China is expected to open next March and the
second from Inchon, South Korea, to Yantai, China, will be
launched next April timed with the completion of a new passenger
terminal in Inchon.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a container route from Pusan, South Korea, to Posjet,
Russia, will be put into operation around next April and a ferry
lane from the South Korean coastal city of Socho to Posjet and to
the Chinese city of Hunchun by land will also be open at the same
time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
