<HEADLINE> Chinese President Speaks Before Leaving for Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua)-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
has said that the Chinese Government's resumption of exercise of
sovereignty over Macao and the establishment of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of the People's Republic of China mark
another important step on the road of China's full reunification.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also General Secretary of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) Central Committee and Chairman of the Central Military
Commission (CMC), made the remarks at a ceremony at the Great Hall
of the People here to see off the Chinese central government
delegation, headed by Jiang, before it was leaving for Macao.
</P>
<P>
The decision by the central government to send a delegation
with wide representation to attend the handover ceremony and
various celebrations in Macao is to demonstrate the strong
solidarity of the Chinese people of all nationalities and all the
compatriots, to illustrate the joyous mood of the Chinese people
for the return of Macao to the motherland, and to show the
resolute support of the central government and all the Chinese
people to the Macao SAR and compatriots in Macao, stressed Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Delegation members, including Zhu Rongji, Qian Qichen and Chi
Haotian, were present at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Seeing the delegation off were Li Peng, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing
and Li Lanqing, among other Party and State leaders.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the ever-growing prosperity and the rise of the
international status of China are the fundamental reason for the
return of Hong Kong and Macao, adding that the great idea of "one
country, two systems" proposed by the late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping is the only correct way for China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the successful practice of the "one country, two
systems" idea in Hong Kong and Macao will serve as a model for the
solution of the Taiwan issue, and facilitate the nation's complete
reunification.
</P>
<P>
All the Chinese people are joyful for the return of Macao to
the motherland, and the world is also paying close attention to
the event, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the success of the ceremonial activities
will have profound and long-term impact on the promotion of
patriotism among the Chinese people, the consolidation of
solidarity among various nationalities in China, stepping up the
process of the full reunification of the motherland, and the grand
cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
While participating in the ceremonial activities, members of
the delegation will demonstrate the glory and pride of the Chinese
people of all nationalities for the return of Macao, show the
courtesy of traditional Chinese culture, and express their deep
brotherhood to compatriots in Macao, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that during its stay in Macao, the delegation will
expound the central government's basic principles and policies
toward Macao after its return to the motherland to the compatriots
in Macao and guests from other countries.
</P>
<P>
The ceremonial activities will show a strong sense of
confidence to the outside world that the Macao SAR will surely be
able to maintain long-term stability and development and that the
prospects of Macao will be rosy under the guidance of the
principles of "one country, two systems", "Macao people governing
Macao" and a high degree of autonomy, said the Chinese president.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the confidence that the delegation will surely
fulfill its glorious task in Macao with the joint efforts of all
its members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
