<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Pakistan Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 18 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were
killed and six others injured in a bomb blast in Pakistan's border
city of Sialkot Saturday, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion device was planted on a bicycle which went off in
early morning in Sialkot's busy Rangpura area. No one has claimed
responsibility for the blast.
</P>
<P>
Police suspected that the terrorist was also killed in the
explosion. They said the device was Indian-made.
</P>
<P>
This is the second bomb blast in Sialkot, located near the
border between Pakistan and India-controlled Kashmir, in the last
four days. In the first blast, three persons were injured.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, ten people were killed and 20 others wounded in a
bomb blast in Pakistan-controlled Kashmir. 
</P>
