<DOCNO> XIE19991218.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korean Parliament Passes 2000 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The South Korean National
Assembly, the country's parliament, passed a budget of 92.6
trillion won (81.9 billion U.S. dollars) for the year 2000 on
Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 126 for, 66 against and one abstention, the
parliament approved the budget, which is slightly smaller than the
one requested by the government but is up 4.7 percent from the
budget this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the parliament allowed the government to issue 10.95
trillion won (9.68 billion dollars) worth of state bonds next year,
less than the 11.5 trillion won (10.17 billion dollars) the
government asked for.
</P>
<P>
Upon the passage of the budget bill, Finance and Economy
Minister Kang Bong-kyung said the government will work for an
early return to balanced finance to pave the way for a better
economy of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
