<HEADLINE> Time Capsule Buried as Witness to Return of Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The "time capsule" for the
landmark return of Macao to China, an airtight metal container of
return-related documents, has been buried today deep into the
ground before the venue for Macao's handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The capsule is expected to be unearthed and opened for public
exhibition 50 years later.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio, who arrived in Macao
yesterday afternoon for the handover ceremony, and Macao Governor
Vasco Rocha Vieira put related documents into the container,
sealed it and buried it in the ground. The documents concern Macao
government's preparations for celebrations of the landmark return,
the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration, and the Basic Law of the
Macao Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Macao is to return to China on Dec. 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
