<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Elected Representatives Asked to Take up Responsibility </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad Saturday reminded Barisan Nasional (BN) (National
Front) elected representatives to take their responsibility to
serve their constituencies seriously.
</P>
<P>
In addition to attending Parliament sessions, the elected
representatives should visit their constituencies and pay
attention to the problems their respective constituencies
concerned, Mahathir, who is BN chairman, said at a news conference
