<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Ruling Party Sets up Anti-Graft Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's ruling Chama
Cha Mapinduzi (CCM) has formed a special ethics unit to curtail
the rampant corrupt practices within the party.
</P>
<P>
The independent Guardian newspaper quoted CCM Secretary General
Philip Mangula as saying Friday that CCM has decided to intensify
the war against the corrupt practice among its leaders and wings.
</P>
<P>
