<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading South African newspapers on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Citizen:
</P>
<P>
-- By the end of next year, South Africa will have about 540
fewer mayors when the current 843 municipalities are reduced to
about 300.
</P>
<P>
Saturday Star:
</P>
<P>
-- Having been brought under control to a certain degree,
malaria is once again rearing its head across the African
continent, killing one child every 20 seconds, and its moving
swiftly south into the warm northern areas of South Africa.
</P>
