<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inter-Korean Trade by Sea More Than Doubled in January-September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The inter-Korean trade by sea
routes in the first nine months this year skyrocketed by 128.4
percent to 885,119 tons compared with the same period last year,
the South Korean Unification Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that 731,724 tons of goods were shipped from
South Korea to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
during the January-September period and 153,395 tons vice-versa.
</P>
<P>
Ulsan led all other ports of South Korea in handling 348,803
tons of goods in the inter-Korean trade, followed by Yosu with 294,
245 tons, Pusan 32,489 tons, Inchon 21,761 tons and Kwangyang 10,
165 tons.
</P>
<P>
Pusan was the leading port in importing 51,980 tons of goods
from the DPRK, followed by Ulsan with 48,616 tons, Inchon 23,169
tons, Kunsan 12,859 tons and Pohang 8,289 tons.
</P>
<P>
The inter-Korean trade has been on the rise since South Korean
President Kim Dae-jung implemented his Sunshine policy toward the
DPRK, which aims to achieve inter-Korean reconciliation as well as
exchange and cooperation based on the principle of separating
politics from business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
