<HEADLINE> Picture Albums on Macao History Sent as Gifts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- China Taxation Publishing
House today presented 400 picture albums on Macao's history to the
Chinese Revolutionary Museum, the Macao Museum and Macao student
representatives.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Pusui, general designer of the albums, said that the
carefully-selected pictures of the albums have demonstrated the
changes in Macao in the past 400 years and its customs and
traditions.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 pictures in the book depict the great events and
dignitaries in its history. With great details and elegant
designing, the album offers comprehensive introduction to the
future special administrative region, the second one in China
after Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
