<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Military Razes Houses, Shops in Aceh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The brutality was triggered by the death of an unidentified
military official who was found early on Friday, it said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that at least two platoons of TNI soldiers and
Brimob arrived at the place and conducted an inspection over the
incident.
</P>
<P>
"But they found no residents as local people had moved to other
place following the discovery (of the dead soldier), because they
were afraid that a revenge attack wound be launched by the
military personnel, the daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Indonesia daily reported Saturday that in North
Aceh regency, 'rain of bullets' had been launched by unidentified
gun-men. At least two people died in the incident.
</P>
<P>
Aceh is the most-western province of Indonesia. It has been
under fire since the demand for independence and separation from
Indonesia was made by some people in the province. But the
Indonesian central government insists that it would not tolerate
any kind of separatism effort in the province.
</P>
<P>
In order to ease tension in the predominantly Moslem province,
the Indonesian government would soon implement a package of
autonomy bill which will allow the local government to enjoy its
natural resources and handle their own matters except defense,
finance and foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
President Abdurrahman Wahid also agreed to try military
officials who were allegedly involved in human right abuse and
atrocities in the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
