<HEADLINE> IFAD Extends Loan for Nepal's Rural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The International Fund for
Agriculture Development (IFAD) will extend a loan assistance of 6.
55 million U.S. dollars to Nepal through Special Drawing Right for
a period of seven years, according to a press release available
here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The release by Nepal Rastra Bank, Nepal's central bank, said
that the loan will be utilized for the ongoing Western Terai
Poverty Alleviation Project, which has been implemented with an
aim to uplift the living standard of the people in 8 districts of
the Western Region of the country.
</P>
<P>
The project is targeted to cover 29,000 poor women by extending
loans on areas such as shallow tube well, skill development and
community development among others, according to the release.
</P>
</TEXT>
