<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Gas Field Found in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Another major gas field has been
discovered in northeastern Bangladesh, newspapers here reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The gas field was discovered recently by the Unocal Corporation
of the United States in Molulvi Bazar district, about 170
kilometers northeast of here.
</P>
<P>
"The Moulvi Bazar gas field discovery will contribute
significantly to the natural gas resource base of Bangladesh,"
Terry Budden, president of managing director of the Unocal
Bangladesh Limited, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The gas field lies on a vast subsurface geologic anti-clinical
structure spanning eight 13 kilometers in length North to South
and two kilometers in width from East to West, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Natural gas is the major energy resource of Bangladesh, which
has an estimated reserve of 30-40 trillion cubic feet, including
13 trillion cubic feet already discovered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
