<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, December 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. construction of new homes and apartments
dropped by 2.3 percent in November to the lowest level in seven
months as mortgage rates kept rising, the Commerce Department said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Department reported that builders started new homes at a
seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.6 million units in November,
the lowest level since 1.58 million units were started in April.
(US-Housing-Decline)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Visiting French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin called
for enhanced cooperation between Japan and France in achieving
economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Japan National Press Club on Friday, Jospin,
who arrived here Thursday for a three-day visit to Japan, said
France and Japan need to adapt their state-oriented social models
to the trend of globalism as affirmed by the United States. (
Japan-France-Globalization)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- Swisscom intends to convert the Blue Window Internet
service into a stock corporation in order to increase its
flexibility for partnerships and encourage even more growth.
</P>
<P>
The Swisscom board of directors has given the go-ahead for
privatization and the resumption of talks with the media company
TA-Media, according to a Swisscom press release Friday. (Swiss-
Internet Service)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazilian Foreign Minister Luiz Felipe
Lampreia said Friday a series of meetings will start next month to
promote the Southern Common Market (Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
He told the press that the first meeting will be held in
Brasilia, capital of Brazil, with the attendance of his Argentine
counterpart Adalberto Giavarini. (Brazil -Mercosur-Meetings)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian vice-Premier Franco Bassanini affirmed Friday
that that there is no need to panic about the Millennium Bug in
Italy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting of the National Decisional Center for
the Change of Data Computer Problem, Bassanini stated that The Y2K
situation seems to be perfectly under control in Italy. (Italy-
Millenium Bug) 
</P>
