<HEADLINE> Number of Indonesia's Poor People Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of Indonesians
living under poverty line has dropped to 37.5 million in 1999 from
49 million by the end of 1997, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
The number of the poor population has been reduced gradually
through the poverty Eradication Program launched by the central
government and sponsored by international community, the national
Antara News Agency Saturday quoted Coordinating Minister for
People's Welfare and Poverty Eradication Basri Hasanuddin as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Hasanuddin also said that the government has allocated 5.7
trillion rupiah (0.8 billion U.S. dollars) for the poverty
eradication program in the 1999/2000 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
"The fund will be used to boost poverty eradication program and
keep the number of the needy people down," Hasanuddin said.
</P>
</TEXT>
