<HEADLINE> Italy Says Millennium Bug Under Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, 17 December (Xinhua) -- Italian vice-Premier Franco
Bassanini affirmed Friday that that there is no need to panic
about the Millennium Bug in Italy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting of the National Decisional Center for
the Change of Data Computer Problem, Bassanini stated that The Y2K
situation seems to be perfectly under control in Italy.
</P>
<P>
Regarding electricity, he said, "We do not foresee the
possibility of instability."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said that the ENI Group, Italy's state-controlled
energy group, has planned for any problems by setting aside
emergency supplies of petrol and natural gas which will last for
over one month.
</P>
<P>
Bassanini said that the possibility of problems with the
national water supply system is "practically non-existent."
</P>
<P>
In addition, Y2K compliance measures have already been
completed in all ports and airports, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
