<HEADLINE> Weekly Highlights of Diplomatic News (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua)-- Following are major diplomatic
news released by Xinhua in the past week:
</P>
<P>
 Albanian President Visits China
</P>
<P>
-- President Rexhep Meidani of the Republic of Albania arrived
in the Chinese capital on Sunday morning, at the start of a state
visit to China.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin, in talks Monday with Albanian
President Rexhep Meidani, said that China respects the
independence, national sovereignty, and territorial integrity of
Albania, as well as the development course chosen by its people.
</P>
<P>
-- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC), in a meeting Tuesday with
Albanian President Rexhep Meidani, said that China and Albania
enjoy friendly ties, and bilateral cooperation in various aspects
has been strengthened in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji also met with President Meidani Tuesday, and
said that China is willing to raise its cooperation with Albania
to a new high in the coming century through joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice-Premier Mourns Late Croatian President
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen went to the Croatian embassy
in Beijing to mourn the death of Croatian President Franjo Tudjman.
</P>
