<P>
U.S. Indictment of Wen Ho Lee A Result of Cold War Mentality
</P>
<P>
-- A Chinese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman traced the U.S.
recent indictment of the Taiwan-born scientist at Los Alamos, Wen
Ho Lee, to the influence of cold war mentality, at a regular news
conference Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the indictment of Lee on December 10 by relevant
U.S. departments, spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said that there are
certain people in the United States who stubbornly stick to the "
cold war" mentality, and purposefully concocted the lie alleging
China's theft of U.S. nuclear technologies.
</P>
<P>
China, U.S. Agree on Compensation for Embassy Bombing
</P>
<P>
-- The Government of the People's Republic of China and the
Government of the United States of America reached an agreement on
December 16, 1999 on the question of compensation relating to the
U.S. bombing of the Chinese Embassy in the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia (FRY), according to Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu
Bangzao.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the U.S. Government will pay a sum
of 28 million U.S. dollars to the Chinese Government for the
property loss and damage suffered by China as a result of the U.S.
bombing of the Chinese Embassy in FRY last May. 
</P>
