<HEADLINE> Mercosur to Resume Talks Next January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Foreign
Minister Luiz Felipe Lampreia said Friday a series of meetings
will start next month to promote the Southern Common Market (
Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
He told the press that the first meeting will be held in
Brasilia, capital of Brazil, with the attendance of his Argentine
counterpart Adalberto Giavarini.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Foreign Ministry, he added, has been preparing
the proposal with the purpose of consolidating the regional bloc,
the most dynamic one in the Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The minister said South Africa, the most important economy of
the African continent, will become a Mercosur member and he will
travel to Pretoria in February to discuss the matter.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on China's forthcoming admission into the World
Trade Organization, Lampreia said the admission of China, the
biggest emerging global economy, will benefit the organization and
the world economy as well.
</P>
<P>
He added that China and Brazil, as the two biggest developing
countries, must tighten their cooperation within the WTO market
and in all areas.
</P>
<P>
Lampreia said of the next millennium world political order. He
said he opposes hegemony in the solution of international affairs,
calling for the creation of a multipolar structure to guarantee
world peace.
</P>
<P>
The Mercosur, founded in 1995, groups Brazil, Argentina,
Paraguay and Uruguay with Chile and Bolivia as its associate
members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
