<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's net foreign
exchange reserves fell by 58 million U.S. dollars to 16.60 billion
dollars in the week ending on December 15 from 16.65 billion
dollars the previous week.
</P>
<P>
"The decline is caused by foreign debt payments and also
project payments," Bank Indonesia said in its weekly report.
</P>
<P>
The country's net foreign exchange reserves still exceeded the
minimum target of 14.3 billion dollars set by the International
Monetary Fund.
</P>
<P>
Gross foreign exchange reserves, which are net reserves plus
outstanding foreign exchange contracts, also fell, dropping to 27.
53 billion dollars from 27.59 billion dollars, the weekly report
was quoted by national newspapers Saturday as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
