<HEADLINE> Romania Aims at Entering Top 15 at Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Exactly 132 Romanian
athletes have qualified so far for the 2000 Summer Olympic Games
while the Eastern European country is aiming at entering the top
15 on medal standings in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
A senior Romanian Olympic Committee official said on Friday
that those who have qualified will compete in 14 events, with
gymnastics having the best gold medal hopes.
</P>
<P>
The other sports which could win a medal for the country
include boxing, athletics, rowing, swimming and weightlifting, he
said, adding that Romania will send a 160-strong delegation to
Sydney.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Romanian athletes have claimed 24 medals, nine of them
gold, in the world or European championships of the Olympic events.
</P>
