<HEADLINE> Applicants for Post-Graduates of 2000 Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 18 (Xinhua) -- A record 329,000 people have
applied to take China's postgraduate examination of 2000, a 22.8
percent increase over last year's figure, according to the College
Students Department (CSD) of the Chinese Education Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The number of graduate applicants has risen 24 percent to reach
166,000 this year. More than half of the applicants are people who
are now working, a jump of 41,000 compared to last year.
</P>
<P>
The CSD has worked with Qinghua University to create a website
containing updated news and information from universities. The
site is meant to help answer students' questions about various
colleges they plan to apply to and to speed up the admissions
process.
</P>
<P>
The site, www.cpge.edu.cn, has received 30,000 visiters since
it opened in November.  
</P>
</TEXT>
