athletes rounded up this year with good results, winning 24
Olympic medals, of which nine were gold, at world and European
championships. "After nearly a quarter of a century, Romanian
handball women players rejoined the Olympic family, by qualifying
for Sydney during the World Championships in Norway," Popper said.
