<HEADLINE> Vialli Handed Euro Touchline Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chelsea manager Gianluca Vialli
will have to watch his side's next Champions League clash from the
stands after being given a one-match touchline ban by European
soccer governing body UEFA.
</P>
<P>
The punishment follows his outburst in the Champions League
game against Lazio in Rome, when he was ordered from the sidelines.
</P>
<P>
Vialli was dismissed from the dugout during the goalless draw
after losing his temper with an official over a decision by German
referee Hellmut Krug.
</P>
<P>
Krug blew for a foul by Tore Andre Flo just as he was lining up
a shot on goal.
</P>
<P>
The normally-reserved Vialli who apologised afterwards will
have to sit in the stands for Chelsea's trip to Olympique
Marseille in March.
</P>
<P>
"I have to accept it. It's part of the game. The referee made
his decision and I have to get on with it," said Vialli.
</P>
<P>
"From my point of view it is a bit disappointing because as a
manager I like to be there for all the matches," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
