<HEADLINE> Canada-U.S. Test Ranges Agreement Renewed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The agreement will be extended for another 10 years following
Friday's exchange of notes, according to a joint statement by
Canadian Foreign Minister Lloyd Axworthy and Defense Minister Art
Eggleton.
</P>
<P>
The Nanoose Bay test ranges facility is jointly operated b the
Canadian forces and the United States navy under the terms of an
agreement initiated in 1965 and renewed in 1976 and 1986,
according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement termed the facility as "Canada's only
instrumented maritime weapons test range," which is used to test
weapons systems and acoustic sensors. 
