<HEADLINE> Rains Killl 85 in Venezuelan Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rains have killed
at least 85 persons and destroyed 3,000 houses in the Federal
District of Caracas, said Friday governor Hernan Gruber.
</P>
<P>
The security agencies, the civil defense, members of the armed
forces and voluntary workers took part in assistance activities
for the victims in the Venezuelan capital, said Gruber.
</P>
<P>
The uninterrupted rains have affected 20,720 people in the
states of Falcon, Miranda, Vargas, Nueva Esparta, Carabobo,Yaracuy
and the Federal District, said the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The National Constitutional Assembly declared Thursday a state
of "national alarm" because of the rains that have caused floods
and collapse of structures in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Authorities cancelled a ceremony on occasion of the 169th
anniversary of the death of Liberator Simon Bolivar, whose image
is continuously exalted by President Hugo Chavez. 
