<HEADLINE> Germany to Provide Cuba With Official Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The German government will
provide Cuba next year with 3 million marks as the start sum of
its first official development aid to Cuba, the Ministry of
Development Aid said Friday in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
This adjustment of the policy toward Cuba has shown that
Germany "is on the same line with its partners in the European
Union," said Development Aid Minister Heidemaria Wieczorek-Zeul.
</P>
<P>
Germany's goal is to "promote Cuba's change toward democracy,"
she said, adding that the sum would also support the opposite
groups in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The German government promised to help Cuba fight against
desertification and drought. The project may last 10 to 12 years
and Germany's total contribution is expected to reach 11 million
marks, the minister said. 
